# Build context for e2e/distributed/Dockerfile.dist is THIS dir (e2e/) — the
# common ancestor of econ/ and distributed/, so both COPY subtrees resolve. Trim
# everything the image does NOT COPY so the remote-builder upload stays small.
#
# Only builds that use e2e/ as their context read this file. The single-machine
# arm builds use a subdir context (e2e/econ, e2e/codex, e2e/claude) and read their
# OWN per-arm .dockerignore, so this file does not affect them.
#
# KEEP: econ/local-docker/{run-benchmark.py,Dockerfile.*,context (incl. vendor/)},
#       econ/{report.py,econ-telemetry.py,econ-tier-cost.py}, distributed/**.

**/.venv
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/*.log
**/.env
**/.env.local
**/node_modules
**/.unerr
**/.DS_Store

# heavy per-run artifacts (never COPYed into the image)
**/out/
**/results/
**/reports/
**/logs/
**/grading/
**/*.tgz

# other arms are not part of the econ fleet image
claude/
codex/

# EXCEPTION to the `**/node_modules` rule above: the econ toolbox vendors econ's
# `.opencode/` as `vendor/dot-opencode/`, and its `.opencode/tool/*.ts` project
# tools `import "@opencode-ai/plugin"` — a workspace dep that lives ONLY under
# `.opencode/node_modules/`. If it's stripped, opencode aborts the whole session
# at startup (UnknownError → econ exit=1, 0 turns, empty patch). Re-include just
# THIS node_modules tree (all other node_modules stay excluded to keep uploads
# small). Negations must come AFTER `**/node_modules` (last match wins).
!**/dot-opencode/node_modules
!**/dot-opencode/node_modules/**
